Remaining Useful Life Prediction (RUL) of 18650 Lithium-Ion Cells¶

Objective- To find patterns in li-ion cell lifecycle for efficency optimization and rul prediction.

Specifications¶

  • Cell Type - 18650
  • Capacity - 2.8 Ah
  • Temperature - 25 Deg C
  • Charging Rate - 0.5C
  • Discharging Rate - 1.5C

Understanding the Dataset¶

Attribute Definations¶

  • Cycle_Index - Refers to one charging and discharging cycle of the cell
  • Discharge Time - Time taken in seconds for the cell to drain completely
  • Decrement 3.6-3.4V - Time taken in seconds for the cell to drain from 3.6V to 3.4V
  • Max. Voltage Discharge - Refers to the maximum voltage of the cell attained after the charging cycle.
  • Min. Voltage Charge - It is the minimum voltage maintained by the cell after the discharging cycle.
  • Time at 4.15V - Time in seconds for which cell maintains a voltage level above 4.15 Volts.
  • Time constant current - Refers to time in seconds for which a stable maximum current is supplied by the cell.
  • Charging Time - Time in seconds for which the cell is being charged for that cycle.
